verbose_text: The amphetamine stimulant lisdexamfetamine has been reported to cause muscle pain, cramping, and stiffness without other serotonin related symptoms.4, 5 While these side effects have been most widely reported with lisdexamfetamine, there are data suggesting that the combination medication dextroamphetamine-amphetamine (also an amphetamine) can cause similar symptoms.6 Muscle pain, cramping, and stiffness without other serotonin related symptoms have not been reported for non amphetamine stimulant medications used in the treatment of ADHD, including the methylphenidate class of medications.
